 2<b><b>."},{"content":"Add masa harina and salt and knead <b><b>3 min\/<b><b>. Transfer to a bowl, cover with cling wrap and refrigerate until needed. Clean mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Filling"},{"content":"Place guajillo, clove, and allspice into mixing bowl and grind <b><b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>.<b> "},{"content":"Add tomatillos, onions, garlic, oil, thyme, marjoram and oregano and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>, then cook <b>15 min\/250°F\/speed <b>."},{"content":"Add water and salt and mix <b>1 min\/speed 5<b>-<b>10<b> <b>increasing speed gradually<b>. Add chicharrónes, stir through with spatula to coat and cook <b>24 min\/212°F\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Divide reserved dough into 12 equal pieces (approx. 3 oz ea.). Working in batches, roll dough into balls and press into a circle (approx. 5 in.) with a tortilla press or between two pieces of cling wrap. Place 1 heaping tbsp (approx. 2 oz) reserved chicharrónes filling in the center and gather the edges towards the top to create a parcel. Pinch and seal the edges, while at the same time applying gentle and even downward pressure, returning it to a smaller disk shape (approx. 3½ in.). Repeat with remaining ingredients."},{"content":"Heat 1-2 tsp oil in a large cast iron pan or heat a comal over medium heat and cook gorditas in batches until dough is cooked through, golden and crispy (approx. 5 min. per side). Drain on paper towels. Serve hot with reserved Salsa."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Garnish Gorditas de Chicharróne with crumbled cotija cheese, Mexican crema, shredded lettuce and\/or chopped cilantro.","Chicharrónes can be ground in the mixing bowl before starting recipe: place 8 oz chicharrónes into mixing bowl and grind <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Pan fry gorditas in hot oil (360°F-370°F) until cooked through and browned (approx. 3-4 min. per side). Drain on paper towels and serve hot."],"basicInfo":["advanced","1h","1h 40m","12 pieces"]}